The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India down Lanka by 140 runs

Visakhapatnam: Indias superb run in the under-19 Afro-Asian meet continued after they defeated Sri Lanka by 140 runs here on Tuesday. 

Opting to bat first, India piled up 293 for the loss of four wickets. In reply, the Lankans were bowled out for a paltry 153 in 34 overs. 

The hosts are currently at the top of the table with 18 points. 

This is their third win on the trot. Earlier in their first match they defeated Bangladesh by four wickets and in the second they defeated South Africa by 102 runs. 

They face Zimbabwe on Tuesday. 

In another match, Pakistan beat South Africa by four wickets at the Port Stadium. Pakistan chasing a victory target of 231, romped home with four wickets in hand. (PTI) 




